Debouncer on search input → avoid firing API/filter call on every keystroke. User types "caveman" = 7 keystrokes. Without debounce = 7 calls. With debounce (e.g. 300ms) = 1 call after typing stops.

**Why it matters:**
- **Performance** — fewer API calls, less server load
- **UX** — no flickering results mid-word, no race conditions where older request returns after newer one
- **Cost** — fewer API calls = lower bill on metered endpoints
- **Rate limits** — less likely to hit throttling

**How it works:** reset timer on each keystroke. Only fire when user pauses ≥ delay threshold.

```js
function debounce(fn, ms) {
  let timer;
  return (...args) => {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), ms);
  };
}

input.addEventListener('input', debounce(handleSearch, 300));
```

Typical delay: 200-500ms. Shorter = more responsive but more calls. Longer = fewer calls but feels laggy.

